title: The Supreme Court Will Take Up Abortion and Gun Cases in Its New Term
description: Amid concerns about ethics  in camp, the Supreme Court is returning to a new term to take up some familiar topics—guns and abortion.

title: What Beyoncé Gave Us
description: 'Calling her Houston performances perfect would, in some ways, belie the many things they achieved,' writes Bryan Washington. 'In that stadium, she expanded possibility.'

title: Putin Says Waging War in Ukraine Defends Russian ‘Sovereignty’
description: Putin's defence comes a year after he signed documents to illegally annex four Ukrainian regions.

title: Borrowers Are Reassessing Their Budgets as Student Loan Payments Resume
description: Millions of Americans must start repaying their federal student loans again in October, with monthly payments averaging hundreds of dollars.

title: Biden Isn’t at Fault for the Looming Shutdown, Says White House Budget Director
description: White House budget director Shalanda Young said “absolutely not" when asked if Biden should bear any responsibility for the shutdown.

title: The Arrest in the Tupac Shakur Killing Is Related to the Biggie Smalls Murder Case
description: The shooting deaths of the two hip-hop luminaries and rivals—Shakur in Las Vegas and Smalls in Los Angeles six months later—have always been culturally inseparable.

title: What Needs to Happen to Tackle Fashion’s Climate Impact
description: Is the fashion industry anxious enough to combat climate change, asks Céline Semaan.
